00235     struct set_ttl {
00236       set_ttl(hql_interpreter_state &state_) : state(state_) { }
00237       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const {
00238         display_string("set_ttl");
00239         char *end_ptr;
00240         double ttl = strtod(str, &end_ptr);
00241         std::string unit_str = std::string(end_ptr, end-end_ptr);
00242         std::transform(unit_str.begin(), unit_str.end(), unit_str.begin(), ::tolower );
00243         if (unit_str.find_first_of("month") == 0)
00244           state.cf->ttl = (time_t)(ttl * 2592000.0);
00245         else if (unit_str.find_first_of("week") == 0)
00246           state.cf->ttl = (time_t)(ttl * 604800.0);
00247         else if (unit_str.find_first_of("day") == 0)
00248           state.cf->ttl = (time_t)(ttl * 86400.0);
00249         else if (unit_str.find_first_of("hour") == 0)
00250           state.cf->ttl = (time_t)(ttl * 3600.0);
00251         else if (unit_str.find_first_of("minute") == 0)
00252           state.cf->ttl = (time_t)(ttl * 60.0);
00253         else 
00254           state.cf->ttl = (time_t)ttl;
00255       }
00256       hql_interpreter_state &state;
00257     };

00305     struct add_column_family {
00306       add_column_family(hql_interpreter_state &state_) : state(state_) { }
00307       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const { 
00308         display_string("add_column_family");
00309         std::string name = std::string(str, end-str);
00310         boost::trim_if(name, boost::is_any_of("'\""));
00311         Schema::ColumnFamilyMapT::const_iterator iter = state.cf_map.find(name);
00312         if (iter == state.cf_map.end())
00313           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("Access Group '") + state.ag->name + "' includes unknown column family '" + name + "'");
00314         if ((*iter).second->ag != "" && (*iter).second->ag != state.ag->name)
00315           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("Column family '") + name + "' can belong to only one access group");
00316         (*iter).second->ag = state.ag->name;
00317       }
00318       hql_interpreter_state &state;
00319     };

00450     struct scan_set_row_prefix {
00451       scan_set_row_prefix(hql_interpreter_state &state_) : state(state_) { }
00452       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const { 
00453         display_string("scan_set_row_prefix");
00454         if (state.scan.row != "")
00455           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("SELECT ROW predicate multiply defined."));
00456         else if (state.scan.start_row != "" || state.scan.end_row != "")
00457           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("SELECT conflicting row specifications."));
00458         state.scan.start_row = std::string(str, end-str);
00459         trim_if(state.scan.start_row, boost::is_any_of("'\""));
00460         state.scan.start_row_inclusive = true;
00461         str = state.scan.start_row.c_str();
00462         end = str + state.scan.start_row.length();
00463         const char *ptr;
00464         for (ptr=end-1; ptr>str; --ptr) {
00465           if (*ptr < (char)0xff) {
00466             state.scan.end_row = std::string(str, ptr-str);
00467             state.scan.end_row.append(1, (*ptr)+1);
00468             ptr++;
00469             if (ptr < end)
00470               state.scan.end_row += std::string(ptr, end-ptr);
00471             break;
00472           }
00473         }
00474         if (ptr == str) {
00475           state.scan.end_row  = state.scan.start_row;
00476           state.scan.end_row.append(1, (char)0xff);
00477         }
00478         state.scan.end_row_inclusive = false;
00479       }
00480       hql_interpreter_state &state;
00481     };

00612     struct scan_set_start_time {
00613       scan_set_start_time(hql_interpreter_state &state_, bool inclusive_) : state(state_), inclusive(inclusive_) { }
00614       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const { 
00615         display_string("scan_set_start_time");
00616         if (state.scan.start_time != 0)
00617           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("SELECT multiple start time predicates."));
00618         time_t t = timegm(&state.tmval);
00619         if (t == (time_t)-1)
00620           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("SELECT invalid start time."));
00621         state.scan.start_time = (uint64_t)t * 1000000000LL + state.nanoseconds;
00622         if (!inclusive)
00623           state.scan.start_time++;
00624         memset(&state.tmval, 0, sizeof(state.tmval));
00625         state.nanoseconds = 0;
00626       }
00627       hql_interpreter_state &state;
00628       bool inclusive;
00629     };
00630 
00631     struct scan_set_end_time {
00632       scan_set_end_time(hql_interpreter_state &state_, bool inclusive_) : state(state_), inclusive(inclusive_) { }
00633       void operator()(char const *str, char const *end) const { 
00634         display_string("scan_set_end_time");
00635         if (state.scan.end_time != 0)
00636           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("SELECT multiple end time predicates."));
00637         time_t t = timegm(&state.tmval);
00638         if (t == (time_t)-1)
00639           throw Exception(Error::HQL_PARSE_ERROR, std::string("SELECT invalid end time."));
00640         state.scan.end_time = (uint64_t)t * 1000000000LL + state.nanoseconds;
00641         memset(&state.tmval, 0, sizeof(state.tmval));
00642         state.nanoseconds = 0;
00643         if (inclusive && state.scan.end_time != 0)
00644           state.scan.end_time--;
00645       }
00646       hql_interpreter_state &state;
00647       bool inclusive;
00648     };

01083             ;
01084

01089                      >> *( COMMA >> column_name[add_column_family(self.state)] ) >> RPAREN )
01090             ;
01091 
01092           access_group_option
01093             = in_memory_option[set_access_group_in_memory(self.state)]
01094             | blocksize_option 
01095             | COMPRESSOR >> EQUAL >> string_literal[set_access_group_compressor(self.state)]
01096             ;
01097 
01098           in_memory_option
01099             = IN_MEMORY
01100             ;
01101 
01102           blocksize_option
01103             = BLOCKSIZE >> EQUAL >> uint_p[set_access_group_blocksize(self.state)]
01104             ;
01105 
01106           select_statement
01107             = SELECT 
01108               >> ( '*' | ( user_identifier[scan_add_column_family(self.state)] >> *( COMMA >> user_identifier[scan_add_column_family(self.state)] ) ) ) 
01109               >> FROM >> user_identifier[set_table_name(self.state)]
01110               >> !where_clause
01111               >> *( option_spec )
01112             ;
01113 
01114           where_clause
01115             = WHERE >> where_predicate >> *( AND >> where_predicate )
01116             ;
01117 
01118           where_predicate
01119             =  ROW >> EQUAL >> string_literal[scan_set_row(self.state)]
01120             | ROW >> DOUBLEEQUAL >> string_literal[scan_set_row(self.state)]
01121             | ROW >> GT >> string_literal[scan_set_start_row(self.state, false)]
01122             | ROW >> GE >> string_literal[scan_set_start_row(self.state, true)]
01123             | ROW >> LT >> string_literal[scan_set_end_row(self.state, false)]
01124             | ROW >> LE >> string_literal[scan_set_end_row(self.state, true)]
01125             | ROW >> STARTS >> WITH >> string_literal[scan_set_row_prefix(self.state)]
01126             | TIMESTAMP >> GT >> date_expression[scan_set_start_time(self.state, false)]
01127             | TIMESTAMP >> GE >> date_expression[scan_set_start_time(self.state, true)]
01128             | TIMESTAMP >> LT >> date_expression[scan_set_end_time(self.state, false)]
01129             | TIMESTAMP >> LE >> date_expression[scan_set_end_time(self.state, true)]
01130             ;
01131 
01132           option_spec
01133             = START_TIME >> EQUAL >> date_expression[scan_set_start_time(self.state, true)]
01134             | END_TIME >> EQUAL >> date_expression[scan_set_end_time(self.state, false)]
01135             | MAX_VERSIONS >> EQUAL >> uint_p[scan_set_max_versions(self.state)]
01136             | LIMIT >> EQUAL >> uint_p[scan_set_limit(self.state)]
01137             | INTO >> FILE >> string_literal[scan_set_outfile(self.state)]
01138             | DISPLAY_TIMESTAMPS[scan_set_display_timestamps(self.state)]
01139             | RETURN_DELETES[scan_set_return_deletes(self.state)]
01140             | KEYS_ONLY[scan_set_keys_only(self.state)]
01141             ;
01142 
01143           date_expression
01144             = SINGLEQUOTE >> ( datetime | date | time | year ) >> SINGLEQUOTE 
01145             | DOUBLEQUOTE >> ( datetime | date | time | year ) >> DOUBLEQUOTE 
01146             ;
01147 
01148           datetime
01149             = date >> time
01150             ;
01151 
01152           uint_parser<unsigned int, 10, 2, 2> uint2_p;
01153           uint_parser<unsigned int, 10, 4, 4> uint4_p;
01154 
01155           date
01156             = lexeme_d[
01157                        limit_d(0u, 9999u)[uint4_p[scan_set_year(self.state)]] >> '-'    //  Year
01158                        >>  limit_d(1u, 12u)[uint2_p[scan_set_month(self.state)]] >> '-' //  Month 01..12
01159                        >>  limit_d(1u, 31u)[uint2_p[scan_set_day(self.state)]]          //  Day 01..31
01160             ];    
01161             
01162 
01163           time 
01164             = lexeme_d[
01165                        limit_d(0u, 23u)[uint2_p[scan_set_hours(self.state)]] >> ':'       //  Hours 00..23
01166                        >>  limit_d(0u, 59u)[uint2_p[scan_set_minutes(self.state)]] >> ':' //  Minutes 00..59
01167                        >>  limit_d(0u, 59u)[uint2_p[scan_set_seconds(self.state)]] >>     //  Seconds 00..59
01168                        !( DOT >> uint_p[scan_set_nanoseconds(self.state)] )
01169             ];
01170 
01171           year
01172             = lexeme_d[ limit_d(0u, 9999u)[uint4_p[scan_set_year(self.state)]] ]
01173             ;
01174 
01175           load_data_statement
01176             = LOAD >> DATA >> INFILE 
01177             >> !( load_data_option >> *( load_data_option ) )
01178             >> string_literal[set_input_file(self.state)] 
01179             >> INTO >> 
01180             ( TABLE >> user_identifier[set_table_name(self.state)]
01181               | FILE >> user_identifier[set_output_file(self.state)] )
01182             ;
01183 
01184           load_data_option
01185             = ROW_KEY_COLUMN >> EQUAL >> user_identifier[add_row_key_column(self.state)] >> *( PLUS >> user_identifier[add_row_key_column(self.state)] )
01186             | TIMESTAMP_COLUMN >> EQUAL >> user_identifier[set_timestamp_column(self.state)]
01187             | HEADER_FILE >> EQUAL >> string_literal[set_header_file(self.state)]
01188             ;
01189
